Assignment 11: Repository Pattern and Storage Abstraction

This assignment introduces the Repository Pattern to separate business logic from storage logic.

Features Implemented

Generic repository interface using Python generics
Entity-specific repositories
In-memory storage using dictionaries
Repository Factory for storage abstraction
Future database repository stub
CRUD unit tests using pytest

Design Choice

A Factory Pattern was used to abstract repository creation and support future storage backends such as databases or file systems.

Benefits

Improved maintainability
Easier testing
Scalability for future persistence layers
Reduced code duplication through generics